      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "As a consequence of new snow and a moderate to strong southeasterly wind, wind slabs will form above the tree line. In addition the new snow-covered wind slabs of the weekend are prone to triggering in some cases still, especially on very steep slopes. <br/> Faceted weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/> <br/> Several medium-sized slab avalanches have been released in the last few days. On Friday on steep slopes small and medium-sized avalanches occurred naturally."
      },
